The paper discusses a framework for knowledge discovery through the visualization of co-occurrences in a dataset. This involves modeling co-occurrences using hypergraphs, which are well-suited for multi-adicity relationships. This suggests that the paper could be relevant to several sub-categories, including cs.AI (which deals with artificial intelligence and machine learning), cs.LG (which deals with machine learning and statistical learning), cs.IR (which deals with information retrieval), cs.SI (which deals with social and information networks), and cs.DB (which deals with databases and information retrieval).
